abstract: U.S. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said that he was optimistic the United States and Britain, soon to be out of the European Union, would strike a trade deal this year and that he had discussed it with Britain's finance minister on Saturday.
snippet: U.S. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said that he was optimistic the United States and Britain, soon to be out of the European Union, would strike a trade deal this year and that he had discussed it with Britain's finance minister on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — U.S. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said that he was optimistic the United States and Britain, soon to be out of the European Union, would strike a trade deal this year and that he had discussed it with Britain's finance minister on Saturday.
headline_main: U.S. Treasury Chief Mnuchin Says Optimistic About U.S.-UK Trade Deal
headline_print_headline: U.S. Treasury Chief Mnuchin Says Optimistic About U.S.-UK Trade Deal

abstract: American seafood exporters  are optimistic  that a new trade deal with China will allow them to claw back into one of the world's biggest markets for lobster, but help might not have arrived in time for the biggest day on the calendar.
snippet: American seafood exporters  are optimistic  that a new trade deal with China will allow them to claw back into one of the world's biggest markets for lobster, but help might not have arrived in time for the biggest day on the calendar.
lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Maine — American seafood exporters are optimistic that a new trade deal with China will allow them to claw back into one of the world's biggest markets for lobster, but help might not have arrived in time for the biggest day on the calendar.
headline_main: China Deal Might Not Bail Out Lobster Industry This New Year
headline_print_headline: China Deal Might Not Bail Out Lobster Industry This New Year

abstract: The main priority for the president’s legal team is not to undermine their own advantage or give wavering moderate Republican senators reasons to support Democratic requests for witnesses and documentary evidence.
snippet: The main priority for the president’s legal team is not to undermine their own advantage or give wavering moderate Republican senators reasons to support Democratic requests for witnesses and documentary evidence.
lead_paragraph: With the odds stacked against him in the Democratic-run House, President Trump refused to send lawyers to participate in Judiciary Committee hearings last month, complaining that he was not given sufficient due process. But he faces a more receptive audience in the Republican-controlled Senate, where the White House has been working in tandem with Senator Mitch McConnell of Kentucky, the Republican majority leader.

headline_main: Trump will face a more receptive audience in the Republican-controlled Senate.

abstract: President Donald Trump  is expected  to draw a crowd — and headlines — Tuesday when he comes to the New Jersey shore to reward newly minted Republican Rep. Jeff Van Drew with a rally for leaving the Democrats  and opposing impeachment.
snippet: President Donald Trump  is expected  to draw a crowd — and headlines — Tuesday when he comes to the New Jersey shore to reward newly minted Republican Rep. Jeff Van Drew with a rally for leaving the Democrats  and opposing impeachment.
lead_paragraph: President Donald Trump is expected to draw a crowd — and headlines — Tuesday when he comes to the New Jersey shore to reward newly minted Republican Rep. Jeff Van Drew with a rally for leaving the Democrats and opposing impeachment.
headline_main: With Trump's Help, NJ's Van Drew Courts Former Foes
headline_print_headline: With Trump's Help, NJ's Van Drew Courts Former Foes

abstract: The president’s lawyers will offer a radically different view of the facts and the Constitution, while seeking to undercut the whole process by painting it as illegitimate and unfounded.
snippet: The president’s lawyers will offer a radically different view of the facts and the Constitution, while seeking to undercut the whole process by painting it as illegitimate and unfounded.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s legal team plans to mount an aggressive defense that looks more like offense on Saturday as it opens its side in the Senate impeachment trial by attacking his accusers as partisan witch-hunters trying to remove him because they cannot beat him at the ballot box.
headline_main: The White House legal team will begin presenting its case.

abstract: Former Attorney General Jeff Sessions, giving a recent campaign speech to a suburban Republican club, recalled his 2016 decision to endorse then-presidential candidate Donald Trump at a time when many party members were uncertain about the bellicose outsider.
snippet: Former Attorney General Jeff Sessions, giving a recent campaign speech to a suburban Republican club, recalled his 2016 decision to endorse then-presidential candidate Donald Trump at a time when many party members were uncertain about the bellico...
lead_paragraph: VESTAVIA HILLS, Ala. — Former Attorney General Jeff Sessions, giving a recent campaign speech to a suburban Republican club, recalled his 2016 decision to endorse then-presidential candidate Donald Trump at a time when many party members were uncertain about the bellicose outsider.
headline_main: Jeff Sessions Stresses Trump Loyalty in Alabama Senate Race
headline_print_headline: Jeff Sessions Stresses Trump Loyalty in Alabama Senate Race

abstract: President Trump’s lawyers appear fairly confident that the Democrats will not have enough votes to call witnesses at trial.
snippet: President Trump’s lawyers appear fairly confident that the Democrats will not have enough votes to call witnesses at trial.
lead_paragraph: When President Trump’s defense lawyers begin to outline their case on Saturday, they will consider everything that Democrats have raised in their own presentation to have opened the door for discussion.
headline_main: White House team plans to refer repeatedly to Hunter Biden.

abstract: The lead House impeachment manager tried to pre-empt the president’s defense.
snippet: The lead House impeachment manager tried to pre-empt the president’s defense.
lead_paragraph: As Representative Adam B. Schiff of California, the lead House impeachment manager, wrapped up the Democrats’ 24-hour presentation of the case for removing President Trump, he took a few moments on Friday night to forecast the defense team’s counterarguments — and sought to shoot them down.

abstract: Iran is not ruling out negotiations with the United States even after an American drone strike that killed a top Iranian general, the country's foreign minister said in an interview released Saturday.
snippet: Iran is not ruling out negotiations with the United States even after an American drone strike that killed a top Iranian general, the country's foreign minister said in an interview released Saturday.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI, United Arab Emirates — Iran is not ruling out negotiations with the United States even after an American drone strike that killed a top Iranian general, the country's foreign minister said in an interview released Saturday.
headline_main: Iranian FM: Tehran Still Willing to Negotiate With US
